{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Refresh exact-pinned dev tooling: zizmor + ruff\n\nBump two exact `==` pins in `pyproject.toml`'s `[dev]` extra to current, un-yanked releases.\n\n## Why\n- **zizmor 1.27.0 is YANKED** for GHSA-f42p-wjw5-97qh (Moderate, CWE-532): 1.27.0 prints\n  GitHub tokens (`GH_TOKEN`/`GITHUB_TOKEN`/`ZIZMOR_GITHUB_TOKEN`) to stderr under `-v`/debug\n  logging. Only 1.27.0 is affected; the fix is 1.28.0. rebar's `make lint` invokes `zizmor\n  release.yml` with no verbose flag, so there is no live exposure, but pinning exactly to a\n  security-yanked release is fragile (a stricter resolver / pruned cache can fail installs).\n- **ruff 0.15.19 -> 0.15.22**: routine patch refresh to stay current on the format/lint pin\n  (exact-pinned for local<->CI parity). No yank/security; grouped here as a low-risk sibling.\n\n## Plan\n1. `pyproject.toml`: `zizmor==1.27.0` -> `1.28.0`; refresh the pin comment that names 1.27.0.\n2. `pyproject.toml`: `ruff==0.15.19` -> `0.15.22`.\n3. Reinstall the dev extra so the worktree venv has the new tools.\n4. Run `make lint`; if the newer ruff reformats anything, apply `ruff format` and include the\n   diff so CI format-check stays green. Run `make typecheck`.\n5. One commit, `rebar-ticket` trailer + DCO sign-off; push to Gerrit; land after\n   `LLM-Review +1` AND `Verified +1`.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `pyproject.toml` line pins `zizmor==1.28.0` (no longer `1.27.0`).\n- [ ] `pyproject.toml` line pins `ruff==0.15.22` (no longer `0.15.19`).\n- [ ] The `[dev]` pin comment above zizmor no longer references the string `1.27.0`.\n- [ ] `make lint` exits 0 in the worktree venv (ruff check + format-check + zizmor + actionlint).\n- [ ] `make typecheck` exits 0 in the worktree venv.\n- [ ] `git diff --stat` on the change shows only `pyproject.toml` (plus any ruff-format churn), no other files.\n- [ ] The change is merged to `main` via Gerrit with `LLM-Review +1` and `Verified +1`."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784743396267155001,"uuid":"645a55cd-0e04-43e5-9bde-ef59cc188737"}